		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message28522685">The gimmick about Baccano! is that while the first episode is purposely more confusing than the others, you end up seeing most of the scenes from that episode in their context as the series goes. So when you do see the scene as it is supposed to be watched, you think "ah, so that's what was going on!", an effect which a linear narrative wouldn't have achieved. Which makes it cool, more useful than what Haruhi 1 did.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
