		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message28549087">I just finished this show, it had been on my ptw for months, and when I saw it was an anime to be discussed here I decided to finally watch it. <br />
<br />
The direction and characters were indeed quite special, but my major issue with the series was that there didn't seem to be a reason WHY the story was told the way it was. In the more successful stories of this nature (Memento immediately comes to mind) the plot's structure provides insight into the character. In Baccano, the structure did not arise from theme, or character, it was just kind of there. <br />
<br />
I also don't require a meaningful theme to enjoy a show (and I did enjoy baccano overall), but I do require one to consider a show better then merely 'good'.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
